aude Code (which creates clean `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` per test), OpenCode has NO data directory isolation\\n- All tests share OpenCode's global user-level data directory\\n- Setup (lines 70-80 in `testutil/repo.go`): Writes `opencode.json` **in the repo directory** (not in OpenCode's config dir) to configure permissions and API key\\n  - Path: `filepath.Join(dir, \\\"opencode.json\\\")`\\n  - Allows external_directory permission and optionally embeds `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\\n- This is a **shared state problem** - concurrent OpenCode tests could interfere with each other's database migrations, node_modules resolution, and cached state\\n\\n### 4. **Test Parallelization & Environment Variable Sharing**\\n\\n**How tests are parallelized:**\\n\\n1. `ForEachAgent` calls `t.Parallel()` (line 121)\\n2. Each agent gets a subtest via `t.Run(agent.Name(), ...)`\\n3. Go's test runner parallelizes independent subtests (within the same test function)\\n4. Concurrency is further gated per-agent via `AcquireSlot` / `ReleaseSlot`\\n\\n**Environment variables:**\\n\\n- **NOT per-test isolated by default** - each test process shares the parent's `os.Environ()`\\n- `main_test.go` (lines 18-69) sets up **global test process environment**:\\n  - Line 34: Prepends `entire` binary dir to PATH\\n  - Line 66: Sets `GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL=/dev/null` to ignore user's git config\\n- Each agent driver decides what env vars to pass:\\n  - Claude: Creates clean `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` + removes `CLAUDECODE` var (lines 116-133)\\n  - Gemini: Adds `ACCESSIBLE=1` (line 89)\\n  - OpenCode: Adds `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` only (line 108)\\n  - **Shared env vars** like `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY` are inherited by all tests\\n\\n**Test repo isolation:**\\n\\n- Each test gets a fresh temp repo via `os.MkdirTemp(\\\"\\\", \\\"e2e-repo-*\\\")` (line 46)\\n- Temp repos are cleaned up after test (line 53) unless `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1`\\n- **Per-repo setup** for opencode: `opencode.json` written to repo root only\\n\\n### Ke